Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.22,0:00:03.31,Wood Shop,sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1573,0)}Wood Shop
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.82,0:00:06.06,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.44,0:00:07.65,Main,egawa,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.65,0:00:09.28,Main,egawa,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't it look awesome?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.30,0:00:11.78,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Ready, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.78,0:00:15.03,Main,all,0000,0000,0000,,We did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.04,0:01:48.08,Episode-Title - Copy,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Seven: The Ofunehiki Shakes
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.08,0:01:50.67,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,You guys did a great job.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.67,0:01:53.42,Main,sayu,0000,0000,0000,,It's all thanks to me and Miuna.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.89,0:01:56.05,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Really? You're actually saying that?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.55,0:02:01.56,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,This really is amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.56,0:02:02.91,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,I'm touched.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.91,0:02:04.20,Main,kiyo,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.20,0:02:05.87,Main,aki,0000,0000,0000,,We really worked hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.87,0:02:07.95,Main,guy,0000,0000,0000,,It was a lot more fun \Nthan I thought it'd be.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.95,0:02:09.02,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.02,0:02:10.90,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,This calls for some popsicles.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.90,0:02:11.77,Main,all,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.77,0:02:13.46,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,I'll treat you guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.46,0:02:16.61,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want Gori Gori-kun \Npops or Homebase Bars?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.61,0:02:17.77,Main,guy,0000,0000,0000,,So cheap!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.77,0:02:20.88,Main,egawa,0000,0000,0000,,Er, Sensei, it's too cold \Nfor popsicles today.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.88,0:02:22.62,Main,egawa,0000,0000,0000,,We even canceled swimming today.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.62,0:02:24.30,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.30,0:02:27.31,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,But sadly, they don't sell \Nmeat buns this time of year.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.31,0:02:29.39,Main,both,0000,0000,0000,,I want to do the Ofunehiki...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.30,0:02:32.77,Main,kiyo,0000,0000,0000,,They said that in unison.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.77,0:02:34.04,Main,sayu,0000,0000,0000,,Hot damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.02,0:02:36.32,Main,egawa,0000,0000,0000,,Talk about close.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.32,0:02:38.26,Main,guy,0000,0000,0000,,They've totally got the hots for each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.32,0:02:39.20,Main,mana,0000,0000,0000,,Th-That's not true! It's not like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.20,0:02:42.09,Main,guy,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now, trying to play it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.09,0:02:44.05,Main,egawa,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder how far they've gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.05,0:02:45.23,Flashback,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.16,0:02:48.81,Italics,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,That hurt...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.60,0:02:51.81,Italics,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,That hurt a lot more than \NI thought it would...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.81,0:02:54.97,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we are going to do it in a sense...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.97,0:02:57.38,Main,tsumu,0000,0000,0000,,No, I don't mean that...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.38,0:02:59.45,Main,tsumu,0000,0000,0000,,But what you taught us in\Nclass that they used to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.19,0:03:03.58,Main,tsumu,0000,0000,0000,,With the sea and the surface \Nworking together...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.58,0:03:04.94,Main,tsumu,0000,0000,0000,,Couldn't we do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.94,0:03:06.50,Main,aki,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, that sounds like a great idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.50,0:03:10.46,Main,kiyo,0000,0000,0000,,Since we went through all the trouble, \Nit'd be nice to see a real Ofunehiki.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.73,0:03:15.77,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,But we wouldn't be able to do it \Nwithout help from Shioshishio...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.77,0:03:17.84,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,so it'd be a little hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.75,0:03:20.92,Main,egawa,0000,0000,0000,,But if we're going to do it, \Nwe want to do it right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.92,0:03:22.08,Main,egawa,0000,0000,0000,,Right, guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.08,0:03:24.44,Main,kiyo,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, since we came this far.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.44,0:03:25.85,Main,aki,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.85,0:03:28.85,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,I understand. I really do understand...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.85,0:03:30.24,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,But because of the disagreements
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.24,0:03:33.33,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,Shioshishio village and the Oshiooshi \Nfishery cooperative have,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.33,0:03:36.10,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,they're saying there \Nwon't be one this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.28,0:03:38.23,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.30,0:03:41.40,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,We went through all this \Ntrouble making it...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.40,0:03:43.68,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do it! A real Ofunehiki!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.68,0:03:45.15,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Hikari...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.15,0:03:46.83,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,Hii-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.83,0:03:48.92,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,I'll do something about Shishio.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.92,0:03:52.22,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Tsumugu, you be the leader and \Ndo something about Oshiooshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.22,0:03:53.44,Main,tsumu,0000,0000,0000,,Hikari...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.44,0:03:56.42,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,You say that, but I think \Nit'd be pretty hard...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.42,0:03:59.27,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,I know, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.65,0:04:01.55,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,I don't like doing \Nthings only halfway.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.55,0:04:05.86,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it's hopeless, I want to at least try \Neverything we can do to finish with no regrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.86,0:04:07.64,Main,egawa,0000,0000,0000,,All right, I'm in!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.64,0:04:08.56,Main,guy,0000,0000,0000,,Me, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.56,0:04:10.22,Main,guy,0000,0000,0000,,Tsumugu, you're in, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.83,0:04:12.48,Main,tsumu,0000,0000,0000,,I don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.48,0:04:13.95,Main,kiyo,0000,0000,0000,,Me too!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.95,0:04:15.02,Main,aki,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds good to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.44,0:04:18.65,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,Great... This is great!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.05,0:04:18.25,Main,egawa,0000,0000,0000,,This will be great!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.25,0:04:18.65,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.65,0:04:20.84,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,This is indeed youth!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.84,0:04:23.09,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,All right. I'll help out as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.09,0:04:24.76,Main,egawa,0000,0000,0000,,Let's all do our best!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.76,0:04:26.32,Main,all,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.32,0:04:27.84,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,That was great, Hii-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.84,0:04:29.21,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone's so great!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.21,0:04:31.95,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,I'll make sure that \Nthe Ofunehiki happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.95,0:04:32.92,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.48,0:04:37.44,Italics,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,The thing that you and \NTsumugu wished for...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.67,0:04:42.80,Ofunehiki a Reality,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Association to Make the Ofunehiki a Reality
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.49,0:04:42.80,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.80,0:04:45.88,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Let's make the Ofunehiki \Na reality again this year!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.37,0:04:48.52,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Please help us get enough signatures!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.52,0:04:50.56,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,Please help us out!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.56,0:04:52.51,Main,bg,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Please help us out!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.57,0:04:53.92,Main,sayu,0000,0000,0000,,All right, we're not going \Nto lose! Right, Miuna?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.51,0:04:55.23,Main,bg,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Let's make the Ofunehiki \Na reality this year!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.92,0:04:55.23,Main,miuna,0000,0000,0000,,R-Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.20,0:04:56.81,Main,bg,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Please help us out!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.81,0:04:58.15,Main,sayu,0000,0000,0000,,Please help us o—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.15,0:05:00.72,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to scare \Npeople off doing that!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.03,0:05:03.64,Main,sayu,0000,0000,0000,,Please help us out!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.64,0:05:05.71,Main,sayu,0000,0000,0000,,We're trying to do the Ofunehiki!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.71,0:05:07.41,Main,miuna,0000,0000,0000,,Th-The Ofunehiki...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.41,0:05:08.83,Main,sayu,0000,0000,0000,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.97,0:05:11.76,Main,both,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.76,0:05:13.83,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Good work, keep it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.83,0:05:15.12,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Please help us out!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.12,0:05:19.45,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,We are Hama Junior High's \N"Association to Make the Ofunehiki a Reality."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.57,0:05:21.42,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Please help us out!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.87,0:05:24.13,Main,man,0000,0000,0000,,I heard they weren't \Ngoing to do it this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.98,0:05:26.36,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,As Hama Junior High's volunteers,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.36,0:05:28.84,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,we plan on doing something \Neven bigger than last year!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.84,0:05:30.52,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you middle schoolers\Nmanage it by yourselves?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.52,0:05:32.65,Main,Manaka,0000,0000,0000,,Please sign!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.65,0:05:34.14,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,We're serious about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.14,0:05:35.10,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Please help us out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.99,0:05:38.85,Main,man,0000,0000,0000,,Guess I don't have a choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.01,0:05:41.32,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.31,0:05:43.36,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Hikari's sort of amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.32,0:05:42.37,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.36,0:05:45.43,Main,tsumu,0000,0000,0000,,Why is he so serious about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.80,0:05:48.93,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,I think he probably wants to get rid of \Nhis frustrations so he's going all out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.93,0:05:51.71,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,To think that Hikari has \Nsuch a competitive side...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.71,0:05:53.52,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,Humans really are pretty deep.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.61,0:05:56.83,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,Ma'am. Pardon me, Ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.83,0:05:59.86,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have a moment?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.21,0:06:03.92,Main,lady,0000,0000,0000,,W-Well, if it's just for a moment...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.92,0:06:06.05,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Talk about "deep"...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.38,0:06:08.19,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,I need to try hard, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.46,0:06:11.94,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,We're doing the Ofunehiki...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.22,0:06:14.78,Main,tsumu,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think that really suits you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.78,0:06:15.93,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.43,0:06:20.04,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Is that really the point here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.54,0:06:23.62,Main,tsumu,0000,0000,0000,,I mean... everyone \Ncan only do what they can.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.62,0:06:27.33,Main,tsumu,0000,0000,0000,,If you try hard at something you \Ncan't do, it only hurts in the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.14,0:06:30.98,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,You're all really going at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.98,0:06:33.08,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,Pretty impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.08,0:06:34.20,Main,miuna,0000,0000,0000,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.58,0:06:38.66,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Akari-san, thank you for \Ntalking to the manager for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.66,0:06:40.08,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.08,0:06:43.67,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,Not to mention Sayama-kun, the \Nmanager's son, is helping out, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.67,0:06:45.63,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,And I'd like to see it, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.63,0:06:47.55,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,A real Ofunehiki.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.55,0:06:50.11,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Then, could you display these in the store?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.81,0:06:52.52,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,You got it! Leave it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.52,0:06:53.89,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,Give me some of those forms, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.89,0:06:56.04,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get you some signatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.04,0:06:58.28,Main,itaru,0000,0000,0000,,Could I get some, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.28,0:07:00.18,Main,itaru,0000,0000,0000,,I'll hand them out to people I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.18,0:07:01.40,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.40,0:07:02.22,Main,itaru,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.22,0:07:06.74,Main,itaru,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, having the people of the \Nsurface and sea hand in hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.15,0:07:09.54,Main,itaru,0000,0000,0000,,It sort of hits pretty close to home.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.40,0:07:13.54,Flashback,both,0000,0000,0000,,I want to do the Ofunehiki.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.30,0:07:18.83,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to make it happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.41,0:07:22.92,Main,itaru,0000,0000,0000,,I look forward to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.92,0:07:24.19,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,It's not happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.19,0:07:25.75,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.75,0:07:27.83,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,We got this many signatures!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.83,0:07:29.88,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,You can at least talk to \Nthe fishing association!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.88,0:07:32.37,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter how \Nmany signatures you get.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.88,0:07:36.64,Do An Ofunehiki,form top,0000,0000,0000,,Let's Do An Ofunehiki This Year!!\N{\fs18}"Association to Make the Ofunehiki A Reality"\NThe Ofunehiki is one of our historical traditions!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.37,0:07:36.64,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,It was Oshiooshi that said they wouldn't \Ndo it this year in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.64,0:07:37.86,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,B-But...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.86,0:07:39.52,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.52,0:07:43.36,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,This is the first time Hikari's been so \Nserious about asking you for something.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.36,0:07:45.86,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of parent does it make \Nyou if you don't at least listen?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.86,0:07:49.08,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,I saw them collecting signatures myself,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.08,0:07:51.94,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,and they were working really hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.34,0:07:55.55,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,The people on the surface won't listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.55,0:07:57.23,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,There's no point in talking to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.23,0:07:58.22,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.22,0:08:03.57,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,I thought that the guys on the \Nsurface were all pigs at first, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.93,0:08:05.53,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,That there's no point \Nin talking to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.85,0:08:09.13,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,And they thought of us as fish...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.13,0:08:10.42,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,so we were even.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.85,0:08:13.46,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,But I was wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.63,0:08:19.24,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,We're not fish, and they're not pigs!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.24,0:08:21.79,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,We're all humans that can \Ncommunicate with each other!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.79,0:08:23.30,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,We're really serious about this!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.30,0:08:24.58,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,It can be just once!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.58,0:08:26.44,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Please get everyone \Ntogether and talk to them!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.49,0:08:29.11,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to rely on me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.22,0:08:32.17,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Then we don't need your help!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.17,0:08:34.48,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Just don't get in our way, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.82,0:08:44.78,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,So everything went okay with \Nthe fishery cooperative?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.78,0:08:47.06,Main,Ise,0000,0000,0000,,It really wasn't that hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.06,0:08:48.00,Main,Ise,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.00,0:08:51.28,Main,tsumu,0000,0000,0000,,Even if people couldn't really \Ntalk about the Ofunehiki,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.28,0:08:53.12,Main,tsumu,0000,0000,0000,,they seemed to be concerned about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.38,0:08:55.62,Main,egawa,0000,0000,0000,,And what about your end?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.62,0:08:57.96,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,My stupid dad wouldn't listen,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.96,0:09:00.44,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,but the Young Men \NCoalition heard me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.44,0:09:04.14,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,If I mention that the people of \Nthe surface already agreed to it,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.14,0:09:05.35,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,it'll work out somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.35,0:09:08.37,Main,ise,0000,0000,0000,,All right. It's finally show time, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.37,0:09:10.24,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,We're gonna do the Ofunehiki!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.24,0:09:12.66,Main,all,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.66,0:09:14.24,Main,egawa,0000,0000,0000,,All right, time for food!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.66,0:09:15.22,Main,kiyo,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Hopefully everything works out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.24,0:09:17.06,Main,egawa,0000,0000,0000,,If we don't hurry up and eat, \Nthere won't be any time to play.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.22,0:09:17.06,Main,aki,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}But they're all so stubborn...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.06,0:09:19.37,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Just watch. I'm going \Nto make this happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.82,0:09:29.22,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Hikari's working really hard...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.22,0:09:30.18,Main,mana,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.18,0:09:33.13,Main,mana,0000,0000,0000,,But Hii-kun's sort of... um...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.43,0:09:36.72,Main,mana,0000,0000,0000,,Different, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.72,0:09:38.22,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Different?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.22,0:09:41.68,Main,mana,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I mean Hii-kun is always \Ntrying really hard...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.68,0:09:45.33,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,But um... this seems to be a \Ndifferent kind of trying hard...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.61,0:09:46.44,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.38,0:09:49.48,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,I think...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.82,0:09:51.94,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,He's trying to change.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.94,0:09:53.36,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,Change?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.95,0:09:56.23,Flashback,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to change.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.26,0:09:58.86,Flashback,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,I want all of us to be together forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.86,0:10:02.07,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,Ch-Change? That's not good!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.35,0:10:04.29,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,We need to hurry and stop Hii-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.29,0:10:06.36,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,Stop him and rewind!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.04,0:10:10.29,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think we can do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.29,0:10:12.04,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.57,0:10:14.67,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Manaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.10,0:10:16.45,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,Chii-chan...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.80,0:10:22.82,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,There are some things that \Nchange even if we don't want them to...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.34,0:10:26.83,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,But once someone decides they're going \Nto change and work really hard at it,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.83,0:10:31.23,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think even the \NSea God could stop them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.11,0:10:42.57,Main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, they did a great job on this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.57,0:10:44.41,Main,B,0000,0000,0000,,That's pretty impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.41,0:10:46.07,Main,C,0000,0000,0000,,Not bad at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.43,0:10:48.58,Main,A,0000,0000,0000,,I think we could actually use this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.04,0:10:51.06,Main,B,0000,0000,0000,,Look at all the details.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.06,0:10:54.66,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,To think that they were able to get \NHikari's dad to come out, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.66,0:10:56.36,Main,mana,0000,0000,0000,,I'm getting nervous.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.36,0:10:59.36,Main,egawa,0000,0000,0000,,Me too. I sort of want \Nto go take a piss.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.36,0:11:01.48,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Then go already, jeez!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.95,0:11:04.17,Main,A,0000,0000,0000,,They even prepared offerings...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.17,0:11:10.25,Main,B,0000,0000,0000,,When we were kids, we made all of these \Nlittle things too, didn't we, Sakishima?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.94,0:11:12.70,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Why'd you come?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.70,0:11:16.28,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,You... really made all this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.28,0:11:17.08,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.08,0:11:20.95,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,The four of us and our friends from \Nthe surface all worked together.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.95,0:11:22.95,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,I see... So that's why.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.02,0:11:27.08,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,Ojoshi-sama's kimono's \Nfold is backwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.08,0:11:27.90,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.90,0:11:29.29,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.29,0:11:30.54,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.71,0:11:33.57,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What are we going to do, Chii-chan?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.57,0:11:35.71,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,We sewed it so the left \Nwould be in front!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.71,0:11:37.34,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,Ojoshi-sama's going to die!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.34,0:11:39.05,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Wha— Calm down!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.22,0:11:43.80,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,We can fix that in no time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.80,0:11:45.31,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Hikari...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.77,0:11:48.27,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,Talk about a preemptive strike.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.64,0:11:50.45,Main,egawa,0000,0000,0000,,No worries!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.45,0:11:51.97,Main,egawa,0000,0000,0000,,We're just getting started.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.28,0:12:01.70,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,It appears that everyone is ready now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.70,0:12:05.70,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be moderating the meeting today.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.70,0:12:08.72,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,So, what do you all think?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.72,0:12:11.63,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,The students worked really \Nhard to make this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.63,0:12:16.92,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,So as their teacher, I'd really \Nlike to see their dream come true.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.92,0:12:22.21,Main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we never objected to doing the \NOfunehiki in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.21,0:12:23.06,Main,B,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.06,0:12:25.84,Main,B,0000,0000,0000,,And festivals shouldn't be disregarded.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.28,0:12:30.56,Main,A,0000,0000,0000,,And it's not like we're \Ngoing to neglect the god.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.56,0:12:32.35,Main,B,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.35,0:12:34.34,Main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Sakishima.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.34,0:12:36.94,Main,A,0000,0000,0000,,The kids went so far to do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.94,0:12:41.04,Main,A,0000,0000,0000,,A lot's happened, but \Nwhy don't we let it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.04,0:12:42.07,Main,B,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.61,0:12:47.68,Main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Well, go ahead and start.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.68,0:12:50.34,Main,teach,0000,0000,0000,,But it's already started...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.34,0:12:51.45,Main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Not that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.89,0:12:54.83,Main,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'm saying that we'll listen \Nto your apology now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.32,0:12:56.56,Main,land a,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.56,0:12:57.93,Main,land b,0000,0000,0000,,Apology?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.93,0:13:00.25,Main,sea B,0000,0000,0000,,We came all the way here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.25,0:13:01.90,Main,sea B,0000,0000,0000,,Apologize to your heart's content.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.90,0:13:04.80,Main,sea B,0000,0000,0000,,Our hearts are as wide as the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.80,0:13:07.98,Main,sea B,0000,0000,0000,,It'll probably be a little \Nrude, but we'll hear it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.98,0:13:11.07,Main,land c,0000,0000,0000,,Why would we have to apologize?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.07,0:13:14.10,Main,sea A,0000,0000,0000,,You're the ones that said you wouldn't \Ndo the festival in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.10,0:13:15.34,Main,land b,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.34,0:13:18.48,Main,land b,0000,0000,0000,,Are you trying to say you don't \Nremember the last Ofunehiki?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.48,0:13:20.64,Main,land A,0000,0000,0000,,You guys were complaining about \Nhow there wasn't enough money
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.64,0:13:24.11,Main,land A,0000,0000,0000,,or enough people, and you asked \Nto scale things down, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.11,0:13:27.17,Main,land C,0000,0000,0000,,Not to mention this happened \Ntime after time...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.17,0:13:28.41,Main,land C,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}At that rate,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.41,0:13:31.17,Main,land C,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}even if we hadn't said we \Nweren't going to do it,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.89,0:13:32.87,Main,egawa,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, this doesn't look \Nvery good, does it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.17,0:13:32.87,Main,land C,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}you guys would have said it yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.87,0:13:34.29,Main,sea a,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.29,0:13:35.71,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Please wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.71,0:13:39.21,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't a gathering to say who \Nshould apologize or who's at faul—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.21,0:13:41.39,Main,guys,0000,0000,0000,,Stay out of it, kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.02,0:13:46.82,Main,sea B,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, you're the ones \Nwho called it off first.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.82,0:13:48.18,Main,sea B,0000,0000,0000,,It's only natural that you apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.18,0:13:49.49,Main,sea a,0000,0000,0000,,Not to mention,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.49,0:13:51.95,Main,sea a,0000,0000,0000,,the reason we don't have \Nenough people or any money
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.95,0:13:54.72,Main,sea a,0000,0000,0000,,is because ya'll keep \Ntaking them from the top!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.72,0:13:55.71,Main,sea b,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.71,0:13:57.56,Main,sea b,0000,0000,0000,,Both our fish and our women!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.56,0:13:58.40,Main,land b,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.40,0:14:01.93,Main,land b,0000,0000,0000,,The reason your women run off is \Nbecause you guys aren't reliable, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.93,0:14:04.81,Main,land a,0000,0000,0000,,You're gonna blame us for that, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.81,0:14:06.36,Main,sea A,0000,0000,0000,,What'd you just say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.24,0:14:15.25,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like it's gonna rain...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.88,0:14:18.19,Main,itaru,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to come, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.49,0:14:19.44,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.44,0:14:21.86,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,Hikari worked really hard...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.16,0:14:25.32,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,so I want to help if I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.85,0:14:26.76,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,Also,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.76,0:14:31.49,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,I really want to show \NMiuna-chan an actual Ofunehiki.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.04,0:14:35.49,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it's because of our roots.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.49,0:14:40.01,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,There's that, and if \NMiuna-chan is ever lost...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.01,0:14:46.40,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it could be like \Na light in her heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.40,0:14:47.77,Main,itaru,0000,0000,0000,,Akari...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.58,0:14:51.75,Main,itaru,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.96,0:14:54.05,Main,itaru,0000,0000,0000,,For thinking about Miuna.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.91,0:14:56.83,Main,itaru,0000,0000,0000,,All right, let's go in.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.20,0:15:00.20,Main,land A,0000,0000,0000,,The hell are you saying, fish head?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.22,0:14:58.35,Main,itaru,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse u—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.20,0:15:01.80,Main,sea a,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up, you pigs!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.80,0:15:04.04,Main,sea a,0000,0000,0000,,All your squealing's annoying!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.04,0:15:05.08,Main,land c,0000,0000,0000,,All right then.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.08,0:15:07.23,Main,land c,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we settle \Nthings once and for all?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.23,0:15:09.30,Main,sea b,0000,0000,0000,,What'd you just say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.69,0:15:13.62,Main,iaru,0000,0000,0000,,Is this a bad time?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.62,0:15:14.66,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.66,0:15:15.56,Main,ise,0000,0000,0000,,That sucks.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.56,0:15:16.93,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Itaru-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.93,0:15:18.52,Main,egawa,0000,0000,0000,,Talk about bad timing...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.52,0:15:21.38,Main,sea a,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! You're the guy Akari's seeing!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.38,0:15:22.18,Main,itaru,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.18,0:15:23.40,Main,sea b,0000,0000,0000,,You thief!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.40,0:15:24.30,Main,itaru,0000,0000,0000,,Thie—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.30,0:15:26.83,Main,sea a,0000,0000,0000,,We've got plenty of things \Nwe want to say to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.83,0:15:27.90,Main,sea a,0000,0000,0000,,Get over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.90,0:15:28.40,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.40,0:15:31.57,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on here? Hikari! Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.57,0:15:33.63,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Would you guys stop already?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.63,0:15:35.62,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,You're adults, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.62,0:15:38.45,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Why can't you talk things out?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.33,0:15:38.95,Main,sea a,0000,0000,0000,,Stay out of the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.86,0:15:57.31,Main,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,Are you satisfied?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.19,0:16:08.69,Looking for Part-Timers,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Looking for Part-Timers!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.21,0:16:14.20,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,Break up with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.99,0:16:20.70,Main,Dad,0000,0000,0000,,As Hikari said, because we're not fish or pigs,\N we can understand each other...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.70,0:16:23.36,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,But it's because we can communicate,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.36,0:16:28.29,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,that we realize there are \Ndifferences we can never get over.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.77,0:16:33.71,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,People from the sea and people from \Nthe surface will never see eye to eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.42,0:16:41.51,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,I always... thought \Nsomething was different.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.90,0:16:44.44,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,I finally realize what it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.06,0:16:49.18,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,I'm talking about Itaru-san and myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.18,0:16:54.82,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,And yet, you always change the \Nsubject to the sea and the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.70,0:17:01.24,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,I asked Mom a long time ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.65,0:17:04.35,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,why she married you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.58,0:17:07.75,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,She said... the reason was simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.75,0:17:12.51,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,She married you just because she loved you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.51,0:17:15.87,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,When I heard that, I was happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.65,0:17:19.06,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,Because of that, I just \Nhappened to ask her,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.06,0:17:22.52,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,what if you were from the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.52,0:17:25.25,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,And then Mom just smiled and said...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.81,0:17:30.23,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,"Even then, I would have \Nbeen with your father."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.70,0:17:35.06,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to be Miuna-chan's mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.78,0:17:51.20,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Are you leaving?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.67,0:17:55.53,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.76,0:17:57.32,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Hikari.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.32,0:17:58.99,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.99,0:18:00.37,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Because I'm leaving, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.22,0:18:02.14,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,But—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.14,0:18:05.16,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Being left alone with Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.39,0:18:07.56,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,I know that there's no way \Nthings will be normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.93,0:18:13.03,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.23,0:18:18.99,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,I see, so she said she's going to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.72,0:18:21.12,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.12,0:18:24.24,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,The shaking's gotten more pronounced.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.69,0:18:27.43,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,There isn't much more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.43,0:18:29.72,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,What are you going to do, Tomoru?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.20,0:18:31.55,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,Uroko-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.84,0:18:35.83,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,Are you leaving?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.83,0:18:36.74,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.13,0:18:39.47,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,Would you consider changing your mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.35,0:18:43.44,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,I will not.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.43,0:18:48.81,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,But you're still under my protection.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.81,0:18:50.97,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for everything \Nthat you've done for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.33,0:18:53.23,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,But I've decided.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.80,0:18:55.82,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,I will live life on the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.18,0:18:57.43,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.06,0:18:59.80,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not coming back, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.66,0:19:12.92,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently everyone in \Nthe family is stubborn.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.28,0:19:15.24,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,Good grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.44,0:19:39.39,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Akari!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.39,0:19:40.32,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,Hikari!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.00,0:19:46.91,Main,tomoru,0000,0000,0000,,Uroko-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.91,0:19:49.97,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,We must do everything we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.81,0:19:54.46,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,Why not give up?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.46,0:19:57.19,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,No good will come of you \Ngoing up to the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.62,0:19:58.89,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,There will!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.89,0:20:01.05,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,There's someone up there \Nwho's waiting for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.05,0:20:04.84,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Uroko-sama! Why are you \Ntrying to stop us?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.35,0:20:06.94,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,Because of a promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.94,0:20:07.93,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,A promise?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.93,0:20:10.30,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,I have to protect you both...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.30,0:20:12.28,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,as you are his descendants.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.15,0:20:17.16,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.68,0:20:24.45,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,You leave me no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.80,0:20:43.24,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.68,0:20:45.43,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,The water temperature suddenly...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.18,0:20:48.60,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't good...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.60,0:20:50.75,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate, we'll freeze...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.49,0:20:54.19,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Like hell I'm going to give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.92,0:20:57.75,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to be... forced \Ninto the flow anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.55,0:21:20.60,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,Well, well, they're definitely \Ngiving it their all.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.60,0:21:21.50,Main,tomoru,0000,0000,0000,,Uroko-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.16,0:21:26.09,Main,tomoru,0000,0000,0000,,Show some mercy... Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.41,0:21:41.76,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Akari, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.76,0:21:43.07,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,R-Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.34,0:21:54.20,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,Are you certain?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.93,0:23:33.61,Main,miuna,0000,0000,0000,,I want a shell from the sea that I love.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.61,0:23:35.62,Main,itaru,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want you to go through \Nthe same thing, Akari.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.62,0:23:38.14,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care if I can't \Ngo back to the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.14,0:23:40.06,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with those \Ntwo being together?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.14,0:23:40.10,Episode-Title - Copy,title,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Eight: \NBeyond the Wavering Feelings
